HEPATITIS A - AUSTRALIA (MELBOURNE) (03)
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Hepatitis A - Australia (Melbourne) 980102000048
Hepatitis A - Australia (Melbourne) (02) 980103112826
Date: Sat, 03 Jan 1998 14:25:12 +1100
From: Mark Veitch <m.veitch@microbiology.unimelb.edu.au>

You can read the full text of the account of the spa-related cluster of
hepatitis A cases in the most recent Communicable Diseases Intelligence,
Vol 21, Number 23, 25 December 1997 - An outbreak of hepatitis A associated
with a spa pool (by Graham Tallis and Joy Gregory) at the following site:
<http://www.health.gov.au/pubs/cdi/cdicur.htm>.
The epidemic curve of known related cases suggests that the index case did
indeed infect the others.
--
